sentences: Tapp died on November 26, 2003, after an assailant shot him four times, three in the face and once in the chest, on the front lawn of the home of his mother and stepfather, Phillip "Tuba Phil" Frazier of Rebirth Brass Band, in the Gentilly neighborhood.
section: == Death ==

sentences: On December 31, 2003, police arrested 22-year-old Garelle Smith in connection with Tapp's murder.
section: == Death ==

sentences: By 2008, Smith had been arrested for three more murders, and, in each case, charges were dropped and he was released due to lack of witnesses and the New Orleans 60-day law.
section: == Death ==

sentences: Smith himself was found shot to death on August 13, 2011.
